10:
Man, these guys suck! How am I
supposed to train if THIS is what
we're up against?
41:
Yeah... For as long as I can
remember. Just the sight of one
sends me into a panic...
43: Sorry for losing my cool back there.
48:
Don't worry about it. A little strange
for folks like you to be afraid of the
undead, though.
50: Shouldn't that be your strong suit?
58:
...All right, I've made up my mind!
Time for some training!
61:
I've gotta train my mind and get
over my fears! Let's go!
65:
What are you planning on doing to
get over your fears, though?
68:
It's all in my head, so I figure the best
way to beat it is to meditate.
80:
All right. In that case... First, just lie
down and relax...
83:
Calm yourself... Breathe... slowly..
Your mind... empty of thoughts...
99: That's how I empty my mind!
102:
A little counterintuitive, don't you
think?!
106:
Well, everyone's got their own way of
doing it. This is my way!
118: ...I don't think I'm cut out for this.
124:
Makani's meditating again today, is
she? She's shut herself away for so
long now.
128:
It's pretty impressive. I can't say I
understand her methods, but she
seems really focused when she's
meditating.
131:
Even still, there is such a thing as too
much training...
136: Heh! No need for you to worry!
142:
Hey, all done with meditation? Have
any good ideas crossed your mind?
146:
Sure did! I finally found an answer to
my problem!
151:
Coming all the way out here to hunt
undead seems a little overboard...
154:
It's hard to say no when her mind's
been made up...
158:
Lilie said that quite a lot of them
would appear here. Are you sure
you want to do this, Makani?
163:
Just leave it to me! I'll show you how
my training's paid off!
193:
Scary things are scary! I'm only
human, you know!
196:
But what's important is
acknowledging your fears and still
moving forward!
198:
You put your fears aside and take
the offensive!
202: Meditation has given me my answer!
207:
Are you sure it's the right answer?!
Not that I mean to judge your
choices here!
212: Yes! I'm TERRIFIED, but I'm still going!
216:
Pretty crazy way to conquer your
fears.
219:
She hasn't... totally lost it yet, so I
think it's working.
